		Read this sample answer to the writing task in the previous exercise and find the mistakes. There are 15. Click on them.
		
		Writing Task 2
</header>
	
<section id="body">
	<img class="rightFloat" src="../Media/TT_AW_015.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"  /><br/><ol id="questionList"></ol>
</section>
<section id="fb1">
	<p align="left"><b>However -> Although</b></p>
</section>
<section id="fb2">
	<p align="left"><b>oppose -> disagree</b><font color="#0000ff"></font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb3">
	<p align="left"><b>On the contrast -> On the contrary</b><font color="#0000ff"></font></p><p align="left"><font color="#000000">We say 'in contrast' and 'on the contrary'. However, they do not mean the same thing!</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb4">
	<p align="left"><b>I am in favour of -> I am convinced that</b><font color="#0000ff"></font></p><p align="left">'in favour of' needs to be followed by a gerund or noun.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb5">
	<p align="left"><b>Another -> The most important</b><font color="#0000ff"></font></p><p align="left">This is the first reason mentioned by the writer.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb6">
	<p align="left"><b>on the other hand -> in turn</b><font color="#0000ff"></font></p><p align="left">The writer is adding another comment supporting the previous idea.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb7">
	<p align="left"><b>The main reason -> The second reason</b><font color="#0000ff"></font></p><p align="left">The 'main' reason has already been discussed in the first paragraph.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb8">
	<p align="left"><b>as -> such as</b><font color="#0000ff"></font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb9">
	<p align="left"><b>including -> for instance</b><font color="#0000ff"></font></p><p align="left">'including' should come before the example is given, not after it i.e. 'including food suppliers'.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb10">
	<p align="left"><b>A final reason -> A further reason</b><font color="#0000ff"></font></p><p align="left">This is not the writer's final argument.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb11">
	<p align="left"><b>A second reason -> A final reason</b><font color="#0000ff"></font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb12">
	<p align="left"><b>against -> in favour of</b><font color="#0000ff"></font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb13">
	<p align="left"><b>For example -> Consequently</b><font color="#0000ff"></font></p><p align="left">This means 'as a result'.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb14">
	<p align="left"><b>In contrast -> Likewise</b><font color="#0000ff"></font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb15">
	<p align="left"><b>support -> believe</b><font color="#0000ff"></font></p><p align="left">'support' needs to be followed by a noun or gerund.</p>
</section>
